    "## **DESops Tutorial 02**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This guide will cover some more particular ways to use the DESops library."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import DESops as d"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## **Outline**\n",
    "* [Other Supervisory Control Methods](#Other-Supervisory-Control-Methods)\n",
    "* [Language Equivalence](#Language-Equivalence)\n",
    "* [Generating Random Automata](#Generating-Random-Automata)\n",
    "* [Unobserverable Reach and the UR Class](#Unobserverable-Reach-and-the-UR-Class)\n",
    "* [Example: Opacity](#Example:-Opacity)\n",
    "* [Example: Sensor Deception Attacks](#Example:-Sensor-Deception-Attacks)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "___\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Other Supervisory Control Methods**\n",
    "\n",
    "There are additional algorithms for solving supervisory control problems implemented in `DESops` in the `supervisor` submodule.\n",
    "\n",
    "Namely, there is an offline implementation of the [VLPPO algorithm](https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007/BF01797138.pdf) and an implementation of the [All Enforcement Structure](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/7286769) (AES) method.\n",
    "\n",
    "These functions use the same mostly the same interface as the supremal sublanguage functions. The input is generally `method(plant, spec, [...])` where [...] are optional parameters. `plant` should be a `DFA`, but `spec` can be either a `DFA` (automata/language based specification) *or* a `set()` of names of states in `plant` (state based specification).\n",
    "\n",
    "However, the information returned by the methods is not uniform. In the case of `supervisor.supremal_sublangauge`, a realization of a supervisor $S$ is implicitly computed, but the `DFA` returned is $S  ||  G$.\n",
    "\n",
    "`supervisor.offline_VLPPO` on the other hand returns a `DFA` which is a realization of the supervisor $S$.\n",
    "\n",
    "Computing a supervisor using the AES methods first requires constructing an arena using `supervisor.construct_arena`, which returns a tuple (`DFA`, `DFA`) where the first item is the AES arena after pruning state violations, and the second item is the complete arena. Then the supervisor must be extracted from the AES arena using `supervisor.extract_arena`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, both the AES and VLPPO methods as implemented in `DESops` will not consider the marked case, *i.e. they always compute the prefix-closed supervisors*. Only `supervisor.supremal_sublangauge` with argument `prefix_closed=False` considers the marked case."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 5 V, 7 E\n",
      "Events: {c, b, a}\n",
      "Euc: {a}\n",
      "Euo: {c}\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "1  :  [('2', a), ('3', b)]\n",
      "2  :  [('5', c), ('4', b)]\n",
      "3  :  [('4', a)]\n",
      "4  :  [('1', c), ('1', a)]\n",
      "5  :  []\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "G = d.read_fsm(\"tests/models/vlppo_tests/plant1.fsm\")\n",
    "print(G)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a state based specification, where state \"5\" in G is unsafe:\n",
    "X_crit = set()\n",
    "X_crit.add(\"5\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 13 V, 20 E\n",
      "Events: {a, b, c}\n",
      "Euc: {a}\n",
      "Euo: {c}\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "('0', '1')  :  [(('5', '2'), a), (('1', '3'), b)]\n",
      "('5', '2')  :  [(('3', '4'), b)]\n",
      "('1', '3')  :  [(('3', '4'), a)]\n",
      "('3', '4')  :  [(('4', '1'), a), (('3', '1'), c)]\n",
      "('4', '1')  :  [(('2', '3'), b), (('5', '2'), a)]\n",
      "('3', '1')  :  [(('4', '2'), a), (('1', '3'), b)]\n",
      "('2', '3')  :  [(('6', '4'), a)]\n",
      "('4', '2')  :  [(('2', '4'), b)]\n",
      "('6', '4')  :  [(('4', '1'), a)]\n",
      "('2', '4')  :  [(('6', '1'), a), (('2', '1'), c)]\n",
      "('6', '1')  :  [(('2', '3'), b), (('4', '2'), a)]\n",
      "('2', '1')  :  [(('6', '2'), a), (('1', '3'), b)]\n",
      "('6', '2')  :  [(('2', '4'), b)]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "S_vlppo = d.supervisor.offline_VLPPO(G, X_crit, event_ordering=[\"b\", \"c\"])\n",
    "S_vlppo_par_G = d.composition.parallel(S_vlppo, G)\n",
    "print(S_vlppo_par_G)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
