      "('5', '1')  :  [(('6', '2'), a), (('1', '3'), b)]\n",
      "('6', '2')  :  [(('5', '4'), b)]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "S_aes = d.supervisor.extract_AES_super(AES_arena)\n",
    "S_aes_par_G = d.composition.parallel(S_aes, G)\n",
    "print(S_aes_par_G)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 0 V, 0 E\n",
      "Events: set()\n",
      "Euc: set()\n",
      "Euo: set()\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "S_scn = d.supervisor.supremal_sublanguage(G, X_crit, prefix_closed=True)\n",
    "print(S_scn)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note that the supremal controllable and normal sublanguage does not exist in this case. AES and VLPPO both compute supervisors which generate incomparable maximal controllable and observable languages (in this case, they occassionally do compute the same maximal language). \n",
    "\n",
    "In the special case where $\\Sigma_{c} \\subseteq \\Sigma_{o}$, all three methods will compute a supervisor with the supremal controllable and observable language. We demonstrate this property using a function in `DESops` to verify language equivalence in the next section."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "___\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Language Equivalence**\n",
    "\n",
    "As an equality check of DFAs, the `compare_language(input1, input2)` function returns whether the input DFAs are language equivalent, i.e. $\\mathcal{L}(G_1) = \\mathcal{L}(G_2)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, the supervisors in the previous section are not necessarily language equivalent:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "True"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# True: computed the same maximal solution. For a quick check, notice how both S_vlppo_par_G and S_aes_par_G have 13 vertices.\n",
    "# False: computed incomparable maximal solutions. S_vlppo_par_G should have 13 vertices, and S_aes_par_G 11 vertices.\n",
    "d.compare_language(S_vlppo_par_G, S_aes_par_G)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the special case $E_{c} \\subseteq E_{o}$, where normality implies observability, we should expect all three supervisory control methods to compute the same supremal controllable and observable supervisor. We will verify this with another example using `compare_language`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Uncontrollable:  {d, c}\n",
      "Unobservable:  {d}\n",
      "All controllable events observable?  True\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "G_po = d.read_fsm(\"tests/models/scn_tests/cn_test4_g.fsm\")\n",
    "H_po = d.read_fsm(\"tests/models/scn_tests/cn_test4_h.fsm\")\n",
    "\n",
    "Euc = G_po.Euc.union(H_po.Euc)\n",
    "Euo = G_po.Euo.union(H_po.Euo)\n",
    "print(\"Uncontrollable: \", Euc)\n",
    "print(\"Unobservable: \", Euo)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find the contrapositive, Euo C Euc ==> Ec C Eo\n",
    "all_uo_are_uc = all(e in Euc for e in Euc)\n",
    "print(\"All controllable events observable? \", all_uo_are_uc)"
   ]
  },
