   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "___\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Unobserverable Reach and the UR Class**\n",
    "\n",
    "For partially observed systems, we often want to compute a state estimate after a string of observable events.\n",
    "\n",
    "The unobservable reach of a state $x \\in X$ under a set of possible unobservable events $\\Sigma_{uo}^{'}$ (not necessarily the same $\\Sigma_{uo}$ as $G$) is defined as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$ UR(x, \\Sigma_{uo}^{'}) = \\{y \\in X; (\\exists t \\in \\Sigma_{uo}^{'\\ *}) [f(x, t) = y]\\} $\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $f: X, \\Sigma -> X$ is a transition function, and $\\Sigma_{uo}^{' *}$ is the Kleene closure of the subset of unobservable events.\n",
    "\n",
    "The unobservable reach is extended to a set of states $B \\subseteq X$:\n",
    "\n",
    "$ UR(B, \\Sigma_{uo}^{'}) = \\cup_{x \\in B} UR(x, \\Sigma_{uo}^{'})$\n",
    "\n",
    "These subset constructions are expensive, and in some cases are computed an exponential number of times. Memoization can greatly speed up these constructions by storing the results of unobservable reach computations.\n",
    "\n",
    "In `DESops`, the `UR` class uses a dictionary (no size limit) to store unobservable reach computations from sets. The cache maps $(B, \\Sigma_{uo}^{'}) \\rightarrow \\{\\emptyset, UR(B, \\Sigma_{uo}^{'})\\}$, and computes the unobservable reach if it isn't found (maps to $\\emptyset$).\n",
    "\n",
    "We can see that the class is used in computing the observer:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "G_rand = d.random_automata.generate(100, 10, num_uc=2, num_uo=2)\n",
    "print(G_rand.UR)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Printing the UR class gives a rough summary of how much has been stored in the cache."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "G_rand_obs = d.composition.observer(G_rand)\n",
    "print(G_rand.UR)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The cache can be emptied using `UR.empty()`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "G_rand.UR.empty()\n",
    "print(G_rand.UR)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Computing observable reach using the UR class\n",
    "\n",
    "We compute the unobservable reach using the method `UR.from_set(set_of_states, events=None, freeze_result=False)`\n",
    "\n",
    "* `set_of_states` is a set of indices of vertices, $B$ above.\n",
    "* `events` is the set of events to consider, $\\Sigma_{uo}^{'}$ above. If it is none (default behavior), the parent's Euo attribute is use ($\\Sigma_{uo}$ associated with $G$)\n",
    "* `freeze_result`: boolean variable, if `True` then `UR.from_set` will store and return a `frozenset()` of states instead of a regular set. This is useful if the state estimates need to be hashable, and generally they need not be mutable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
