    "___\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Example: Sensor Deception Attacks**\n",
    "\n",
    "The `SDA` submodule extends `DESops` by considering systems under sensor deception attacks.\n",
    "Here we have the system $G$ with a set of *compromised events*, denoted $\\Sigma_a$ where $\\Sigma_a \\subseteq \\Sigma$. The behavior of a sensor deception attack is captured by *inserted* and *deleted* events. That is, events $e \\in \\Sigma_a$ which the attacker *inserts*, such that the supervisor $H$ observes a ficticious event which did not actually occur in $G$, are modeled by a subscripted $e_i$. And events $e \\in \\Sigma_a$ which the attacker *deletes*, such that $e$ occurred in $G$ but was not observed by $H$, are modeled by a subscripted $e_d$. \n",
    "\n",
    "We represent these subscripted events by using user-defined keyword arguments in the `Event` class initialization, where an `Event` object is *inserted* if it has the keyword attribute `inserted=True`, and *deleted* if `deleted=True`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "e, inserted : True\n",
      "e, deleted : True\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "event = d.Event(\"e\")\n",
    "inserted_event = d.Event(\"e\", inserted=True, deleted=False) # e_i\n",
    "deleted_event = d.Event(\"e\", inserted=False, deleted=True)  # e_d\n",
    "print(inserted_event)\n",
    "print(deleted_event)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here, we outline the process for constructing a modified supervisor $\\tilde{H}$ which is robust to sensor deception attack on events in $\\Sigma_a$.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 4 V, 7 E\n",
      "Events: {c, a, b}\n",
      "Euc: {c}\n",
      "Euo: {c}\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "1  :  [('3', b), ('2', a)]\n",
      "3  :  [('1', b), ('4', a)]\n",
      "2  :  [('1', a), ('4', b), ('3', c)]\n",
      "4  :  []\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "G = d.read_fsm(\"tests/models/SDA_tests/robust/rob_arena_ex1.fsm\")\n",
    "X_crit = set()\n",
    "X_crit.add(\"4\")\n",
    "Ea = set()\n",
    "Ea.add(d.Event(\"b\"))\n",
    "print(G)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First we construct a robust arena, using `SDA.construct_robust(G, X_crit, Ea, A=None)` where `G` is the plant automaton, `X_crit` is a state-based specification on `G` in the form of a set of names of states, `Ea` is the set $\\Sigma_a$, and `A` is the attack strategy (default None corresponds to the all-out attack strategy)\n",
    "\n",
    "The `SDA.construct_robust` function computes an arena which captures the plant-supervisor-attacker dynamics, and allows us to subsequently solve a supervisory control problem. We can then extract a *robust* supervisor $H$, if it exists, which enforces the specification under the attack strategy."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 26 V, 46 E\n",
      "Events: {b, deleted : True, frozenset({c}), b, inserted : True, a, frozenset({c, a}), b, frozenset({c, b}), c, frozenset({c, a, b})}\n",
      "Euc: {b, deleted : True, c, frozenset({c}), b, inserted : True, a, b}\n",
      "Euo: {b, deleted : True, b, inserted : True}\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "Q1({,1,})  :  [('Q2({1},{c,b},None)', frozenset({c, b})), ('Q2({1},{c,a},None)', frozenset({c, a})), ('Q2({1},{c},None)', frozenset({c})), ('Q2({1},{c,a,b},None)', frozenset({c, a, b}))]\n",
      "Q2({1},{c,b},None)  :  [('Q2({3},{c,b},None)', b, deleted : True), ('Q1({,3,})', b), ('Q2({1},{c,b},b)', b, inserted : True)]\n",
      "Q2({1},{c,a},None)  :  [('Q1({,2,})', a)]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "arena = d.SDA.construct_robust_arena(G, X_crit, Ea)\n",
    "print(arena.summary(use_state_names=True, lines=3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Any of the methods for computing a controllable and observable supervisor included in `DESops` can be used here. Note that normality here implies observability, meaning the supremal controllable and normal sublanguage computed by `supervisor.supremal_sublanguage` will be equivalent to the maximal controllable and observable languages computed by VLPPO and AES."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 8 V, 66 E\n",
      "Events: {b, deleted : True, frozenset({c}), b, inserted : True, a, frozenset({c, a}), b, frozenset({c, b}), c, frozenset({c, a, b})}\n",
      "Euc: {b, deleted : True, c, frozenset({c}), b, inserted : True, a, b}\n",
      "Euo: {b, deleted : True, b, inserted : True}\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "0  :  [('0', b, deleted : True), ('0', b, inserted : True), ('0', a), ('1', frozenset({c, a})), ('6', frozenset({c, b})), ('5', frozenset({c})), ('0', b), ('0', c)]\n",
      "1  :  [('1', b, deleted : True), ('1', b, inserted : True), ('3', a), ('1', frozenset({c, a})), ('1', frozenset({c, b})), ('1', frozenset({c, a, b})), ('1', frozenset({c})), ('1', b), ('1', c)]\n",
      "2  :  [('2', b, deleted : True), ('2', b, inserted : True), ('2', a), ('6', frozenset({c, b})), ('4', frozenset({c})), ('2', b), ('2', c)]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "arena_spec = d.supervisor.offline_VLPPO(arena, arena.X_crit)\n",
    "print(arena_spec.summary(use_state_names=True, lines=3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 13 V, 17 E\n",
      "Events: {b, deleted : True, frozenset({c}), b, inserted : True, a, frozenset({c, a}), b, frozenset({c, b}), c, frozenset({c, a, b})}\n",
      "Euc: {b, deleted : True, c, frozenset({c}), b, inserted : True, a, b}\n",
      "Euo: {b, deleted : True, b, inserted : True}\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "('Q1({,1,})', '0')  :  [(('Q2({1},{c},None)', '5'), frozenset({c})), (('Q2({1},{c,a},None)', '1'), frozenset({c, a})), (('Q2({1},{c,b},None)', '6'), frozenset({c, b}))]\n",
      "('Q2({1},{c},None)', '5')  :  []\n",
      "('Q2({1},{c,a},None)', '1')  :  [(('Q1({,2,})', '3'), a)]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "arena_sup = d.composition.parallel(arena, arena_spec)\n",
    "print(arena_sup.summary(use_state_names=True, lines=3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The final step is to extract the supervisor $\\tilde{H}$ from the pruned arena (`arena_sup` here), using `SDA.select_robust_supervisor(arena_sup)`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 2 V, 1 E\n",
      "Events: {c, a, b}\n",
      "Euc: set()\n",
      "Euo: set()\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "0  :  [('1', a)]\n",
      "1  :  []\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sup = d.SDA.select_robust_supervisor(arena_sup)\n",
    "print(sup)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "DFA : 2 V, 1 E\n",
      "Events: {c, a, b}\n",
      "Euc: {c}\n",
      "Euo: {c}\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "('1', '0')  :  [(('2', '1'), a)]\n",
      "('2', '1')  :  []\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "G_par_sup = d.composition.parallel(G, sup)\n",
    "print(G_par_sup)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Stochastic attacks and PRISM model checker\n",
    "\n",
    "The `SDA` submodule also implements algorithms for constructing optimal attack strategies in the nondeterministic case, where the plant $G$ is a probablistic automaton (`PFA` here). An attack strategy is optimal in the sense that the *attacked system* $A || G$ is more likely to violate a specification than any other attack strategy, and of those equally likely, the attack strategy with the least number of actions taken.\n",
    "\n",
    "First, we convert the system and specification into an MDP arena which captures the interactions of the supervisor, attacker and environment. We then use the [PRISM probabilistic model checker](https://www.prismmodelchecker.org/) to compute the attack strategies.\n",
    "\n",
    "Using these functions requires PRISM (tested for version 4.6, although it may work for previous versions). An argument to the `SDA.MDP_max_reachability` function is `prism_path`, which expects a path-like variable to the PRISM installation, e.g. *`/path/to/prism-<version>-<...>/bin/`*."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pathlib\n",
    "\n",
    "# need to adjust this:\n",
    "path_to_prism = \"prism-4.6-linux64/bin/\"\n",
    "prism_path = pathlib.Path(path_to_prism)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "PFA : 4 V, 8 E\n",
      "Events: {rN, rE, rW, rS}\n",
      "Euc: set()\n",
      "Euo: set()\n",
      "Source | (Target, Event), ...)\n",
      "1  :  [('3', rE), ('2', rN)]\n",
      "2  :  [('4', rE), ('1', rS)]\n",
      "3  :  [('1', rW), ('4', rN)]\n",
      "4  :  [('2', rW), ('3', rS)]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "G = d.read_fsm(\"tests/models/SDA_tests/stochCostAttack/test_p_g.fsm\")\n",
    "H = d.read_fsm(\"tests/models/SDA_tests/stochCostAttack/test_p_h.fsm\")\n",
    "\n",
    "Ea = set()\n",
    "Ea.add(d.Event(\"rE\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "X_crit = set()\n",
    "X_crit.add(\"4\")\n",
    "print(G)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
